WEBVTT

00:03.738 --> 00:06.071
Previously on The Royals...

00:06.073 --> 00:08.007
- Maybe I find you...
- Pathetic.

00:08.009 --> 00:09.608
Attractive.

00:10.745 --> 00:14.480
I want you to be devoted
to my wellbeing full-time.

00:15.016 --> 00:17.116
- You wanna get out of here?
- Absolutely.

00:17.118 --> 00:20.619
You have an opportunity
to inspire us.

00:20.755 --> 00:23.022
Maybe the answer
isn't walking away.

00:24.091 --> 00:26.592
Maybe you should try and
change it from the inside.

00:27.528 --> 00:29.528
Yesterday, when you found me
in an alley...

00:29.530 --> 00:32.031
Not in an alley.
I found you in the park.

00:32.033 --> 00:34.800
This was hanging around my neck the
night before the King was killed.

00:34.802 --> 00:37.770
- What does it mean?
- We figure this out,

00:37.772 --> 00:40.172
we figure out who's been
killing my family.

00:40.174 --> 00:42.408
And then we make them pay.

00:43.477 --> 00:45.511
I hope I didn't keep
you waiting.

00:45.513 --> 00:47.246
I'd wait a lifetime for you.

00:50.184 --> 00:52.284
It's nothing personal,
Captain Lacey.

00:52.286 --> 00:54.820
- (Gunshot)
- You tell me what you did!

00:54.822 --> 00:57.122
He's dead.

00:59.527 --> 01:02.194
Are you holding?
Come on, hook a girl up.

01:02.196 --> 01:04.063
I can't help you, okay?

01:04.065 --> 01:08.133
Ouch! Feisty princess.

01:08.135 --> 01:11.103
- What is this?
- An early birthday present.

01:11.105 --> 01:13.572
Oh, my...

01:13.574 --> 01:16.275
You and diamonds,
like gin and tonic,

01:16.277 --> 01:18.377
are destined for each other.

01:18.379 --> 01:20.279
So, what's your poison?

01:20.281 --> 01:22.714
Drugs? Booze? Boys?

01:22.716 --> 01:25.584
- Yes!
- Okay, I hear that.

01:25.586 --> 01:28.153
- I'm Len.
- Mandy.

01:28.155 --> 01:30.289
I was happy
when I saw you in my bed.

01:33.160 --> 01:35.828
You fell in love with her.
You know how I know?

01:35.830 --> 01:38.764
You had her in your pocket,
you didn't follow through.

01:38.766 --> 01:41.166
Don't worry because we're
stealing that diamond

01:41.168 --> 01:42.701
and getting the hell
out of here.

01:42.703 --> 01:44.403
Together.

01:47.641 --> 01:50.542
♪ Just let it be ♪

01:50.544 --> 01:54.113
♪ Why don't you be you ♪

01:54.115 --> 01:56.448
♪ And I'll be me? ♪

01:56.450 --> 01:59.618
♪ Come on, let it go ♪

01:59.620 --> 02:02.788
♪ Just let it be... ♪

02:02.790 --> 02:06.558
Ha ha ha! I think we broke
James on the ride back,

02:06.560 --> 02:09.728
probably about after the
ninth repeat in a row.

02:09.729 --> 02:12.798
Trust me,
James has seen far worse

02:12.800 --> 02:17.669
like that time he was being
personally tortured

02:17.671 --> 02:20.739
by Saddam Hussein in Kuwait,

02:20.741 --> 02:22.741
or wherever the hell
that was.

02:22.743 --> 02:25.677
Not even close.
Night, ladies.

02:27.781 --> 02:30.282
You are going to look
so banging

02:30.284 --> 02:31.717
for the party tomorrow night.

02:31.719 --> 02:33.886
I mean, all this PLUS your
gran's earrings?

02:34.889 --> 02:36.855
Damn, girl. Come with me.

02:40.227 --> 02:42.261
You have to.
You're the birthday girl,

02:42.263 --> 02:43.896
you get what you want.

02:43.898 --> 02:46.565
Have them set it in the
necklace and voila.

02:46.567 --> 02:49.301
But it's not even mine.
It belongs to the people.

02:49.303 --> 02:51.203
Trust me, the people want
their princess

02:51.205 --> 02:52.738
to wear it for her birthday.

02:52.740 --> 02:55.374
It's just not as pretty
behind glass.

02:55.376 --> 02:57.876
It needs to be let out and
taste freedom once in a while.

02:57.878 --> 03:01.813
I'm sure they would rather see
it on you than your uncle.

03:02.950 --> 03:06.652
Are you sure
it's not too much, though?

03:06.654 --> 03:09.288
I mean, our birthdays are
always just a reason

03:09.290 --> 03:11.623
for my mother to throw
a hoity-toity gala.

03:11.625 --> 03:13.425
They're never even about us.

03:13.427 --> 03:15.894
Was that supposed to be
a reason for not wearing it?

03:15.896 --> 03:18.864
You deserve to be the center
of attention on a normal day.

03:18.866 --> 03:21.500
Your birthday? No-brainer.

03:22.736 --> 03:24.469
♪ Long way down ♪

03:29.910 --> 03:32.911
♪ It's a long way down ♪

03:34.882 --> 03:37.549
- Another one in that corner.
- (Laughs)

03:41.889 --> 03:43.622
♪ It's a long... ♪

03:45.259 --> 03:46.992
♪ A long way down ♪

03:46.993 --> 03:48.894
<font color="#ff0000">Sync and corrections by btsix
www.addic7ed.com</font>

03:48.896 --> 03:51.763
Congratulations are in order,
Your Majesty.

03:51.765 --> 03:54.766
Your Succession Bill quietly
passed late last night

03:54.768 --> 03:56.802
with barely the margin
we needed.

03:56.804 --> 03:58.670
And with Moorefield ready

03:58.672 --> 04:01.406
to declare the princesses unfit
the moment Cyrus dies,

04:01.408 --> 04:03.275
you are a heartbeat away

04:03.277 --> 04:05.877
from becoming the reigning
monarch of Great Britain.

04:05.879 --> 04:08.981
And, with Lucius and Cyrus
dominating the headlines,

04:08.983 --> 04:12.284
people won't even notice
the succession has changed.

04:12.286 --> 04:14.720
That is to say, no one knows.

04:19.660 --> 04:22.561
It's nice when all your
hard work pays off.

04:22.563 --> 04:24.596
Wouldn't you say,
Your Majesty?

04:27.501 --> 04:29.001
Your Majesty?

04:29.003 --> 04:32.971
Clear my schedule.
And give me your car keys.

04:39.780 --> 04:42.314
What of the gala
for the twins tonight?

04:44.852 --> 04:47.286
They deserve their own day.

04:47.288 --> 04:49.021
So do I.

