05:02.469 --> 05:04.503
(ALL) Happy Birthday!

05:09.910 --> 05:11.977
- I'm hit.
- Not in the face!

05:14.381 --> 05:16.014
Please! Have mercy.

05:16.984 --> 05:19.351
The pain! The pain!

05:19.353 --> 05:21.420
- You guys are so weird.
- Help.

05:21.422 --> 05:23.555
- How did you know?
- It's not a dorm room.

05:23.557 --> 05:25.424
It's a palace.
I have security.

05:25.426 --> 05:27.693
Is the Queen's high society
birthday party

05:27.695 --> 05:30.996
- still in effect tonight?
- The guest list is ancient.

05:30.998 --> 05:33.432
It's alright. Some of those
old timers can party.

05:34.835 --> 05:37.502
Any royal cougars?

05:51.819 --> 05:53.585
Is that...?

05:53.587 --> 05:56.121
The Crown Jeweler will set
it in the necklace for me!

05:56.123 --> 05:58.423
But I talked him into five
minutes with it

05:58.425 --> 06:01.026
so that I could
"plan my outfit."

06:02.062 --> 06:03.929
- Gimme, gimme!
- Sshh!

06:03.931 --> 06:06.898
There are two guards out
there for this thing

06:06.900 --> 06:10.736
who would flip if they knew someone
else had their mitts on it.

06:11.372 --> 06:12.537
(Text alert)

06:17.111 --> 06:20.812
Of course. Rachel says my
mother's not even coming.

06:20.814 --> 06:22.881
We should just cancel.

06:22.883 --> 06:25.617
I mean, our birthdays have
always been more about her

06:25.619 --> 06:28.086
and her old boring friends
than us, anyway.

06:29.056 --> 06:31.056
Just some lame excuse
for a gala,

06:31.058 --> 06:33.925
each year more boring
than the last.

06:34.895 --> 06:36.695
Even when you guys were kids?

06:36.697 --> 06:38.997
Not even one
special birthday?

06:40.033 --> 06:43.001
Once. It was our ninth.

06:43.003 --> 06:46.772
The Queen was away on some
official trip to Toronto,

06:46.774 --> 06:50.108
so my dad threw us, like,
a real kids' birthday party.

06:50.110 --> 06:54.179
Carnival games, the whole
deal. We had dodgems, even!

06:54.948 --> 06:57.015
I'm sorry, what-ems?

06:57.017 --> 07:00.118
Dodgems! The little cars you
smash into each other with.

07:00.120 --> 07:02.087
Ohhh... bumper cars.

07:02.089 --> 07:05.857
Sure.
And he had this cake made

07:05.859 --> 07:07.759
that we had to jump out of.

07:09.530 --> 07:11.096
Hold this.

07:12.132 --> 07:14.032
I gotta go.

07:14.034 --> 07:16.802
You're a model
who blew off her gig.

07:16.804 --> 07:18.937
Where could you possibly
have to be?

07:18.939 --> 07:22.174
Well, it may or may not have
to do with your birthday.

07:22.176 --> 07:24.609
Which is NOT being canceled,
by the way.

07:24.611 --> 07:27.179
[NOTHING BUT THIEVES:
Graveyard Whistling]

07:27.181 --> 07:29.147
Just trust me.

07:31.118 --> 07:33.185
Okay.

07:34.922 --> 07:37.823
♪ Graveyard whistling ♪

07:38.125 --> 07:40.025
(SIGHS)

07:40.027 --> 07:42.994
♪ And no one's
getting younger ♪

07:42.996 --> 07:44.796
(SIGHS)

07:44.798 --> 07:46.765
I told you I'd be happy
to help.

07:46.767 --> 07:49.601
And I told you
I don't like pity.

07:50.637 --> 07:53.738
But thank you. I've got it.

07:53.740 --> 07:56.241
Ugh! Mother's milk!

07:56.243 --> 07:58.577
Will you be well enough
for the gala tonight?

07:58.579 --> 08:00.045
What gala?

08:00.047 --> 08:02.714
- For the twins' birthday.
- As if.

08:02.716 --> 08:05.250
How is it those bastards'
birthday again?

08:05.252 --> 08:07.085
Because it's on the same day
each year.

08:07.087 --> 08:09.187
And it's been a year since
the last one.

08:09.189 --> 08:11.890
I don't know how many days
I have left on this earth,

08:11.892 --> 08:13.792
but I know I won't waste them

08:13.794 --> 08:15.694
celebrating
those little shits.

08:15.696 --> 08:15.961
What do you want to do, then?

08:20.934 --> 08:24.903
High time I took my
girlfriend on a proper date.

08:24.905 --> 08:26.705
Enchanting.

08:26.707 --> 08:28.240
And where shall we go?

08:28.242 --> 08:31.009
Have you ever been
to the opera?

08:33.080 --> 08:34.779
♪ The cloud I'm living under ♪

08:34.780 --> 08:37.948
♪ When I go there, will I find
my sense of wonder? ♪

08:39.219 --> 08:41.219
♪ Open up the gates ♪

09:09.283 --> 09:10.682
Helena.

09:16.223 --> 09:18.290
We need to talk.

09:29.136 --> 09:30.302
Hey.

09:30.304 --> 09:31.703
Euch!

09:31.705 --> 09:33.038
Eleanor.

09:33.040 --> 09:35.173
You still work here?

09:35.175 --> 09:37.075
Please.
Just one question. Please.

09:37.077 --> 09:39.077
Fine, if it means you'll be
gone quicker.

09:39.079 --> 09:40.712
Come on.

09:40.714 --> 09:42.314
How well do you really
know Mandy?

09:42.316 --> 09:44.082
What is it about this girl

09:44.084 --> 09:46.117
that's got everyone's
knickers in a twist?

09:46.119 --> 09:47.819
Including your own.

09:47.821 --> 09:50.889
I'm happy. Doesn't anybody
care that I'm happy?

09:50.891 --> 09:53.258
Of course I do. But aren't
you moving a little fast?

09:53.260 --> 09:56.094
She's stayed over almost
every night last week.

09:56.096 --> 09:59.064
Sorry, what business is that
of yours?

09:59.066 --> 10:01.666
I'm getting really sick
of trying to find ways

10:01.668 --> 10:04.069
to tell you that I am sick
of you and your games.

10:04.071 --> 10:05.837
Get over it.

10:05.839 --> 10:08.206
Stop being such a jealous
ex-bodyguard.

10:08.208 --> 10:10.809
I just want to make sure
you're protected.

10:10.811 --> 10:14.245
You don't get the privilege
of protecting me any longer.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.982
Thank God.

10:40.140 --> 10:43.775
- Lady Holloway.
- Your Majesty.

10:45.145 --> 10:47.245
I'll get some wine.

10:52.653 --> 10:56.254
You are truly
a petulant disgrace.

10:56.256 --> 10:59.157
You make a mockery of
the country and the crown.

10:59.159 --> 11:00.892
First with
your pitiful tirade,

11:00.894 --> 11:03.995
then flaunting this pitiful
bimbo around in public.

11:03.997 --> 11:06.665
All this, not to mention
what you did to my husband.

11:06.667 --> 11:09.968
Promising he'd be Prime
Minister, then reneging.

11:09.970 --> 11:12.170
Maybe you should ask
Mr. Holloway the truth

11:12.172 --> 11:14.072
about why our deal is off.

11:14.074 --> 11:16.007
You two will have a lot
to talk about.

11:16.009 --> 11:17.876
Where is he tonight,
by the way?

11:17.878 --> 11:20.311
Working hard after you
shafted him.

11:20.313 --> 11:22.781
More like working
someone's hard shaft.

11:22.783 --> 11:26.985
Enjoy the show. I hear
there's a surprise ending.

11:33.160 --> 11:35.193
So once I've poured
enough liquor down her,

11:35.195 --> 11:37.429
I'll get her alone and switch
the real one for that.

11:37.431 --> 11:40.198
Not bad for 3500 bucks,
right?

11:40.200 --> 11:42.367
I mean, convincing enough
on its own,

11:42.369 --> 11:44.769
but five drinks,
and she'll never know.

11:46.006 --> 11:48.740
You did that thing
with the camera?

11:48.742 --> 11:51.042
Looped a decoy feed, or
I wouldn't be standing here.

11:51.044 --> 11:54.312
It was literally in my hands
hours ago!

11:55.248 --> 11:57.882
Dude! Snap out of it.

11:57.884 --> 11:59.984
This was your plan.

11:59.986 --> 12:02.454
You fell for her, I get it,

12:02.456 --> 12:04.289
because you have a dick
and she's hot.

12:04.291 --> 12:06.324
But time to come back
to reality.

12:06.326 --> 12:09.260
For what we've been talking
about for two years.

12:09.262 --> 12:11.796
We are so close.

12:14.101 --> 12:17.268
You remember that night we took that
guy at the Bellagio for ten grand?

12:17.871 --> 12:22.974
I was so excited and you were
your typical Jasper self,

12:22.976 --> 12:26.010
all "it's cool, no big deal."

12:28.081 --> 12:32.016
Then we, uh... celebrated...

12:32.018 --> 12:34.052
on his penthouse balcony.

12:36.323 --> 12:39.457
I'll never forget what you
said to me after that.

12:39.459 --> 12:41.326
You were done
with those jobs.

12:41.328 --> 12:43.528
After watching your parents
scrape by

12:43.530 --> 12:45.897
on small score
after small score,

12:45.899 --> 12:47.465
you were done.

12:48.835 --> 12:50.535
Then what did you say to me?

12:55.308 --> 12:56.975
You just need one great job.

12:56.977 --> 13:01.212
And that looks like one hell
of a great job to me.

13:10.323 --> 13:12.457
Have you heard from them?

13:12.459 --> 13:14.425
Your folks?

13:15.829 --> 13:18.296
Last I heard,
they were being evicted

13:18.298 --> 13:20.865
from Desert Oasis
Trailer Park.

13:22.836 --> 13:26.371
You're so close to proving
that you're not your dad.

13:27.974 --> 13:29.941
That you're smarter than him.

13:31.044 --> 13:33.344
More talented than him.

13:33.346 --> 13:35.246
That you have better taste...

13:35.248 --> 13:37.048
in everything.

13:45.425 --> 13:47.358
- How...?
- Once you lied to the world,

13:47.360 --> 13:50.361
I knew I was a dead man. So I was
prepared when they walked in.

13:50.363 --> 13:52.430
Alistair, I need you
to know that I,

13:52.432 --> 13:56.167
No, Helena, this is where
I speak and you listen.

13:56.403 --> 13:59.103
I realize now that it's
always been about you,

13:59.105 --> 14:00.905
that I was your convenience.

14:00.907 --> 14:02.440
I'm meant to be grateful

14:02.442 --> 14:04.375
for whatever time I had with
you, and I was.

14:04.377 --> 14:06.377
For 30 years.

14:06.379 --> 14:08.947
Until you dragged Henry's
name through the mud.

14:08.949 --> 14:10.615
That really woke me up.

14:10.617 --> 14:13.318
So, yes, I'm alive.
But not to you.

14:13.320 --> 14:16.487
Not anymore.
To you, I'm dead forever.

14:19.226 --> 14:21.860
That's the speech I'd
prepared to give you.

14:22.562 --> 14:25.163
Until I remembered the kids.

14:25.165 --> 14:28.132
Are they my kids?

14:28.134 --> 14:30.535
Or was that just another lie?

14:30.537 --> 14:33.605
In all truthfulness, I don't
know if the twins are yours.

14:33.607 --> 14:36.407
In the back of my mind,
I've always wondered.

14:37.644 --> 14:41.613
Believe me, Alistair,
this is not a lie.

14:41.615 --> 14:44.449
I promise I will never lie
to you again.

14:45.418 --> 14:47.652
It's the kids' birthday
party tonight.

14:49.022 --> 14:50.455
And yet you're here.

14:50.457 --> 14:53.358
Stuck in your own head,
like you always are.

14:53.360 --> 14:55.026
Never
considering anyone else.

14:55.028 --> 14:56.594
That's not true, Alistair.

14:56.596 --> 14:59.330
Not when we were here,
when we were young,

14:59.332 --> 15:01.499
before I got caught up
in a tide

15:01.501 --> 15:04.469
bigger than any one person
could bear.

15:09.342 --> 15:12.644
I'm not the cruel person
you're making me out to be.

15:12.646 --> 15:15.313
You still had a choice,
Helena.

15:15.315 --> 15:18.449
Everything you've done
has been for one purpose:

15:18.451 --> 15:20.285
getting yourself
on the throne.

15:20.287 --> 15:22.553
And with this new
Succession Bill,

15:22.555 --> 15:25.556
it's all coming together
the way you always wanted.

15:25.558 --> 15:28.159
None of this
is the way I wanted it.

15:28.161 --> 15:31.029
You think I'd have chosen for
things to turn out how they did?

15:31.031 --> 15:33.231
Maybe so.

15:33.233 --> 15:35.433
But you've never had
to sacrifice anything

15:35.435 --> 15:39.070
while everyone around you
continues to lose everything.

15:39.940 --> 15:43.041
Don't you see the twins
are the only ones left?

15:43.043 --> 15:45.176
Hold on to what little
you have left with them

15:45.178 --> 15:46.945
because without them,

15:46.947 --> 15:49.480
you'll be completely alone.

16:07.701 --> 16:09.968
Everybody is looking up here.

16:09.970 --> 16:11.536
The way you look,
you should be used

16:11.538 --> 16:14.539
- to eyes in your direction.
- This is different.

16:14.541 --> 16:16.274
I feel ashamed.

16:16.276 --> 16:18.276
Like I've done
something wrong.

16:18.278 --> 16:20.211
Am I a disgrace to the crown?

16:20.213 --> 16:22.080
Nonsense.

16:22.082 --> 16:25.984
You're an inspiring vision
of peace and purity.

16:25.986 --> 16:30.154
It's those Philistine bitches
who are the disgrace.

16:30.156 --> 16:33.725
Darling, know that with you
by my side,

16:33.727 --> 16:36.294
the crown has never
shone brighter.

16:36.296 --> 16:39.097
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDS)

16:43.470 --> 16:46.471
I can't see a bloody thing.
This is so absurd.

16:46.473 --> 16:50.208
Oh, my God!
And now we're turning.

16:50.210 --> 16:52.477
Whoa, hey. Get on your side.

16:52.479 --> 16:56.180
Sshh! Just relax.

16:56.182 --> 16:58.216
She's so sweet. She went to
so much trouble.

16:58.218 --> 17:00.184
Just try and smile
and be happy.

17:02.756 --> 17:04.655
(Cheering and applause)

17:15.535 --> 17:19.203
Dodgems?
In the bloody palace?

17:19.204 --> 17:21.472
How the hell
did you do all this?

17:21.473 --> 17:24.742
Luckily, you guys roll with one of the
best party-throwers on the planet.

17:24.743 --> 17:27.244
All I had to was distract you
and swipe your phone

17:27.247 --> 17:30.381
- and steal Holden's number.
- You sneaky bitch.

17:30.383 --> 17:32.350
This is insane!

17:32.352 --> 17:35.553
But it looks like not everyone got
the memo on the change of plans.

17:38.725 --> 17:40.425
(Laughter)

17:42.395 --> 17:46.097
Okay. Make sure that you're outside
at midnight for the fireworks,

17:46.099 --> 17:48.399
when it officially
becomes your birthday.

17:48.401 --> 17:50.368
All of this is just foreplay.

17:50.370 --> 17:52.437
At midnight,
shit is about to go off.

17:52.439 --> 17:54.439
Everything looks so amazing.

17:54.441 --> 17:57.108
You look amazing.

17:58.478 --> 18:01.345
This necklace, even better
than I imagined.

18:02.282 --> 18:05.283
No one's ever done anything
like this for me.

18:05.285 --> 18:07.185
Well, that is a damned shame.

18:07.187 --> 18:08.419
[ZERBIN: World's On Fire]

